        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 7 at 10:05PM CDT until July 7 at 11:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Deaf Smith County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 1100 PM CDT.

* At 1005 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 10 miles east of Glenrio to 5 miles northwest of
Bootleg to 5 miles northwest of Rhea, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

* Locations impacted include...
Simms and Bootleg.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Large hail, damaging wind, and continuous cloud to ground lightning
are occurring with these storms. Move indoors immediately. Lightning
is one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
